                                <support><p>A grey limestone block, damaged to varying degrees on three sides. The left margin is intact; the upper edge is lightly damaged; the right margin is lost, extensively so across the lower right corner; the lower margin may be intact at the lower left corner, but is partially abraded. The surviving part of the inscribed face is damaged across the top margin (line 1), across the upper right corner (lines 1-3), and along the bottom margin (line 6) , although showing some wear;  the lower right portion is lost.</p>
